instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The system employs a model‑driven framework that defines a modular architecture with explicit extension points. Core components include a BIM‑based static model, a real‑time data ingestion layer built on Eclipse Hono, a digital‑twin state management service provided by Eclipse Ditto, and a 3‑D visualization front‑end realised with Unreal Engine. Orchestration is achieved by coupling Hono’s MQTT/HTTP gateways to Ditto’s twin management APIs, while the framework automatically generates runtime interfaces from domain semantics. Resource management is handled through the modular plug‑in mechanism, allowing independent deployment of each component and coordinated lifecycle via a central configuration service."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The framework defines a four‑stage life‑cycle: (1) Device Modeling – Building Control Engineers enrich BIM with sensor, actuator and controller entities; (2) Model Extraction – Model‑Driven Engineering (MDE) transforms the enriched BIM into a structured meta‑model; (3) Artifact Generation & Deployment – the meta‑model is automatically compiled into deployable DT services and runtime containers; (4) Operation & Maintenance – real‑time data exchange synchronises the physical building with the deployed twin, while facility managers monitor and control via interactive visualisation. Transitions are managed by automated model‑to‑code pipelines and governed by role‑based responsibilities (engineer, manager, DT engineer) as defined in Table I."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model fidelity is addressed by extending static BIM geometry with behavioral definitions for sensors, actuators, and control logic, thereby reducing the semantic gap between the physical building and its digital replica. Validation is implied through the MDE workflow that automatically extracts structured representations from the enriched BIM and generates deployable DT artifacts, minimizing manual errors. Continuous real‑time data exchange serves as an implicit verification mechanism, ensuring that the digital state reflects the physical reality. No explicit procedures for uncertainty quantification, error correction, or formal quality‑assurance processes are described in the provided documents."
]

